title: FC Baltika-Tarko Kaliningrad
text: FC Baltika-Tarko Kaliningrad () was a Russian <a href="association%20football">football</a> team from <a href="Kaliningrad">Kaliningrad</a>. It played professionally for one season in the <a href="Russian%20Second%20Division">Russian Second Division</a> in 2004, when in came 15th in the West Zone. It was cooperating with <a href="FC%20Baltika%20Kaliningrad">FC Baltika Kaliningrad</a> as its farm club, but was not formally owned by FC Baltika. After the 2004 season it was dissolved.
